			    <HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  	Punky:  I agree that there exists a certain drag-race mentality in the game, as is evident by some of my earlier posts (I think I used the terminology &quot;race-like mentality&quot;), but I don't think the object of the game should necessarily be changed, I simply think there should be more than one object to the game.  I think once a player learns all there is to know about Archspace part of the allure and fun is lost, and by adding different objectives the game might expand and become multi-dimensional rather than existing in its current one-dimensional state.  For those of us &quot;newbs&quot; who have yet to explore the vast world of Archspace, it sometimes seems unfair that our time in this game is cut short by the best players.  Especially in recent sets when the Empire is destroyed faster and more efficiently than ever.  I think I've made all the suggestions I can make, and any more repetition on my part would simply be annoying.  In my mind it's out of my hands, and into the hands of the mods.			   <P align=right></P>
